Prerequisites:
2 CPUs or more
2GB of free memory
20GB of free disk space
Internet connection
Container or virtual machine manager such as: Docker, QEMU, Hyperkit, Hyper-V,  KVM, Parallels, Podman, VirtualBox, or VMware Fusion/Workstation


Steps:
Launch ubuntu20 Instance and add security group all traffic and instance type t2.xlarge
Connect to terminal and type apt-get update -y
Install Docker from official website:
1.	Set up Docker's Apt repository.
# Add Docker's official GPG key:
sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get install ca-certificates curl gnupg
sudo install -m 0755 -d /etc/apt/keyrings
curl -fsSL https://download.docker.com/linux/ubuntu/gpg | sudo gpg --dearmor -o /etc/apt/keyrings/docker.gpg
sudo chmod a+r /etc/apt/keyrings/docker.gpg

# Add the repository to Apt sources:
echo \
 "deb [arch="$(dpkg --print-architecture)" signed-by=/etc/apt/keyrings/docker.gpg] https://download.docker.com/linux/ubuntu \
 "$(. /etc/os-release && echo "$VERSION_CODENAME")" stable" | \
sudo tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/docker.list > /dev/null
sudo apt-get update

2.	Install the Docker packages.
sudo apt-get install docker-ce docker-ce-cli containerd.io docker-buildx-plugin docker-compose-plugin
Install and configure Kubectl:
Link: https://r2schools.com/how-to-install-minikube-on-ubuntu-22-04-lts/
1.	Download the latest release with the command:
curl -LO "https://dl.k8s.io/release/$(curl -L -s https://dl.k8s.io/release/stable.txt)/bin/linux/amd64/kubectl"
2.	Download the checksum file.
curl -LO "https://dl.k8s.io/$(curl -L -s https://dl.k8s.io/release/stable.txt)/bin/linux/amd64/kubectl.sha256"
3.	Validate the kubectl binary against the checksum file:
echo "$(cat kubectl.sha256)  kubectl" | sha256sum --check
4.	Install kubectl using below command:
sudo install -o root -g root -m 0755 kubectl /usr/local/bin/kubectl
5.	Now verify the kubectl version.
kubectl version --client --output=yaml

Download and install minikube:
Link: https://r2schools.com/how-to-install-minikube-on-ubuntu-22-04-lts/
6.	Run the below command to download the minikube binary.
curl -LO https://storage.googleapis.com/minikube/releases/latest/minikube-linux-amd64
7.	Install the minikube
sudo install minikube-linux-amd64 /usr/local/bin/minikube
8.	Now verify minikube version:
minikube version
Configure to Run docker without sudo as below:
adduser swhizz
Enter password and confirm password
press enter and at last press Y
usermod -aG sudo swhizz
su - swhizz
sudo groupadd docker
sudo usermod -aG docker $USER && newgrp docker
Start Minikube and check status as below:
sudo minikube start - -nodes 3 - - driver=docker - -wait=false
minikube status
Verify Cluster Information as below:
kubectl get nodes
